  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bank Audi Equity</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The expected development impact includes (i) increased South-South investment and regional integration; (ii) greater access to SME finance; (iii) private sector development and sharing of banking sector best practices in host countries/emerging markets; and (iv) promotion of environmental and social management systems</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project consists of US$60 million equity investment in Bank Audi s.a.l, (the Bank).  IFCs investment is part of a wider capital increase by the Bank of US$300 million.  The Bank is the largest bank in Lebanon with presence in 13 countries offering a full range of products and services that cover commercial and corporate banking, retail and individual banking, on-line brokerage, private banking and investment banking.  The proposed project is aimed at strengthening the Banks capital base and funding the Banks expansion within and outside Lebanon.</narrative>
  </description>
